covered: Valid Request scenarios including default GET (TC01), paginated (TC02, TC05), and empty/edge cases (TC06, TC07) are covered.
Pagination handling with offset/limit and boundary cases (TC02, TC05, TC07, TC21).
Query parameter validation and edge cases (TC08- TC16, TC14, TC15).
Audit parameter coverage (FULL/MINIMAL/NONE) and regression cases (TC03, TC04, TC19, TC20).
Error handling including bad input (400/422), unauthorized (TC12), system failure (TC13), and timeout (TC22).
State variation and regression tests (TC21, TC19, TC20).
gaps: Rate limiting/throttling tests are not present (e.g., 429 responses under load).
Caching behavior and caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) are not tested.
403 Forbidden authorization scenario not explicitly tested (only 401).
More extensive concurrent load testing beyond 50 parallel requests could be added.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests and verify 429 responses if applicable.
Add tests for caching headers and verify cache behavior.
Include 403 Forbidden authorization tests for RBAC scenarios.
Extend performance tests with varied datasets and longer runtimes, and additional boundary values.
